WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:07.340
[knife slices]

2
00:00:09.509 --> 00:00:10.677
[knife slices]

3
00:00:13.513 --> 00:00:14.639
[Chief Counsel sighs]

4
00:00:14.723 --> 00:00:17.267
[in Korean]
Local residents are complaining

5
00:00:17.350 --> 00:00:21.021
that our land purchase will force
more coyotes into neighborhoods.

6
00:00:21.730 --> 00:00:27.944
Find out who the swing votes are. and
donate to the NGOs they're associated with.

7
00:00:28.486 --> 00:00:29.821
Understood.

8
00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:34.826
I wish kiwis had more crunch.

9
00:00:35.827 --> 00:00:39.330
Next matter is regarding our partnership
dispute with Seoul University.

10
00:00:39.414 --> 00:00:41.624
Just threaten to cut all funding.

11
00:00:41.708 --> 00:00:43.126
They can't strong-arm us.

12
00:00:45.295 --> 00:00:48.465
If the Korean pear and kiwi could be combined…

13
00:00:48.548 --> 00:00:50.425
...that'd be delicious. no?

14
00:00:50.508 --> 00:00:53.094
Yes. that could be very delicious.

15
00:00:54.345 --> 00:00:56.097
Now. the final matter is regarding...

16
00:00:56.598 --> 00:00:58.475
the death at Trochos.

17
00:00:59.350 --> 00:01:00.685
What now?

18
00:01:00.769 --> 00:01:02.937
The police are continuing to ask questions.

19
00:01:03.021 --> 00:01:06.441
Everyone we've bribed is remaining silent. but...

20
00:01:06.524 --> 00:01:10.028
...the police will reach out to
Eunice and Woosh soon.

21
00:01:10.111 --> 00:01:11.488
That's fine.

22
00:01:11.571 --> 00:01:13.073
They don't know anything.

23
00:01:13.156 --> 00:01:14.699
No need to worry.

24
00:01:14.783 --> 00:01:18.620
I mean. I wasn't either when they
didn't know anything. but...

25
00:01:18.703 --> 00:01:20.622
Once the authorities reach out...

26
00:01:21.122 --> 00:01:25.710
...Eunice or Woosh could look into
the ongoing payments out of the club.

27
00:01:25.794 --> 00:01:28.463
[sighs] This is such a headache!

28
00:01:29.464 --> 00:01:30.507
[sighs]

29
00:01:31.466 --> 00:01:35.386
The whole reason I remarried
was because he was fun.

30
00:01:35.470 --> 00:01:39.265
Someone to eat with.
To travel with. That's all.

31
00:01:39.766 --> 00:01:43.686
Since we can't open
any shell companies at the moment.

32
00:01:43.770 --> 00:01:48.525
we need to establish a legitimate cash
flow between the club and Trochos.

33
00:01:48.608 --> 00:01:50.693
If I wanted drama...

34
00:01:50.777 --> 00:01:53.696
I would have stayed with my first husband.

35
00:01:54.197 --> 00:01:57.325
I was considering
Woosh's medical tourism packages.

36
00:01:57.826 --> 00:02:01.788
We could offer a similar program.
officially sanctioned by the country club...

37
00:02:02.705 --> 00:02:04.290
I'll say it again...

38
00:02:04.374 --> 00:02:09.546
...the more clean money flowing
between the club and Trochos. the better.

39
00:02:09.629 --> 00:02:10.922
[Park sighs]

40
00:02:11.631 --> 00:02:13.800
Woosh will hate that--
[distant clattering]

41
00:02:18.847 --> 00:02:20.849
[suspenseful music playing]

42
00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:28.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

43
00:03:01.014 --> 00:03:02.390
[music fades]

44
00:03:02.473 --> 00:03:04.642
[theme music playing]

45
00:03:11.232 --> 00:03:15.987
[in English] Okay. So we are agreed
that we sell the house.

46
00:03:16.487 --> 00:03:18.489
and we each get our portion
of the down payment back.

47
00:03:18.573 --> 00:03:19.824
Adjusted for inflation.

48
00:03:20.325 --> 00:03:21.826
Adjusted for inflation.

49
00:03:21.910 --> 00:03:24.412
And whatever profit we get.
we split it 50-50.

50
00:03:24.913 --> 00:03:25.997
-Easy.
-Great.

51
00:03:26.080 --> 00:03:26.915
Done.

52
00:03:26.998 --> 00:03:29.417
And then. uh. we agree

53
00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:33.546
that I will be the sole custodian
of Burberry going forward.

54
00:03:34.047 --> 00:03:38.218
I do want you
to reconsider naming him that… but yes.

55
00:03:38.885 --> 00:03:40.428
Thank you for the feedback.

56
00:03:40.511 --> 00:03:41.721
You're welcome.

57
00:03:42.805 --> 00:03:44.474
Great. we are flying through this.

58
00:03:45.308 --> 00:03:47.602
I'm just so glad
we can be mature about it.

59
00:03:48.937 --> 00:03:51.105
Okay. so should we. um.

60
00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:53.483
talk about the announcement?

61
00:03:53.983 --> 00:03:55.652
I've drafted up a post.

62
00:03:57.528 --> 00:03:58.571
Oh. did you?

63
00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:01.199
Yeah. it's just a… just a rough draft.

64
00:04:01.282 --> 00:04:02.158
Oh.

65
00:04:03.201 --> 00:04:05.495
You don't wanna wait
until things are finalized?

66
00:04:06.079 --> 00:04:07.121
What's the rush?

67
00:04:07.622 --> 00:04:11.000
It's been a month since we decided.
We need to let people know at some point.

68
00:04:11.084 --> 00:04:12.543
-[Lindsay scoffs]
-Um…

69
00:04:12.627 --> 00:04:14.212
-Can you just read it?
-Yep.

70
00:04:14.295 --> 00:04:17.799
I… I kept it super vague.
just… trials and triumphs.

71
00:04:17.882 --> 00:04:20.385
Uh. we're still each other's biggest fans.

72
00:04:20.468 --> 00:04:22.387
Please respect our privacy at this time.

73
00:04:22.887 --> 00:04:23.721
No.

74
00:04:24.931 --> 00:04:27.600
You have to pick a new photo.
The caption's awful as well.

75
00:04:27.684 --> 00:04:28.601
Um…

76
00:04:29.435 --> 00:04:33.481
Okay. Just. uh. pick a photo.
and tell me what to post.

77
00:04:34.482 --> 00:04:35.483
[Lindsay] Mm-hmm.

78
00:04:38.987 --> 00:04:40.405
[pensive music playing]

79
00:04:40.488 --> 00:04:44.033
Uh. did you sign
your contract extension yet?

80
00:04:45.118 --> 00:04:46.536
Uh. no. I told you.

81
00:04:46.619 --> 00:04:48.621
Park's going back and forth
with the language still.

82
00:04:48.705 --> 00:04:49.622
[Lindsay] Oh.

83
00:04:51.124 --> 00:04:52.125
That's convenient.

84
00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:55.753
What does… what does that mean?
Convenient?

85
00:04:55.837 --> 00:04:58.089
I'm not the one that's delaying it.
She is. okay?

86
00:04:58.172 --> 00:04:59.632
-[Lindsay] Mm-hmm.
-Okay.

87
00:05:02.051 --> 00:05:03.761
Don't fuck me over. Josh.

88
00:05:03.845 --> 00:05:06.472
I'm not gonna fuck you over. Jesus.

89
00:05:09.017 --> 00:05:10.018
What?

90
00:05:11.686 --> 00:05:12.603
Nothing.

91
00:05:14.397 --> 00:05:15.815
You just look different.

92
00:05:21.112 --> 00:05:22.905
[Austin] So cumulatively speaking.

93
00:05:22.989 --> 00:05:27.785
we actually owe $27.802.

94
00:05:27.869 --> 00:05:29.579
How is that even possible?

95
00:05:30.079 --> 00:05:33.291
Well. the hospital was out of network.
so we have to cover half.

96
00:05:33.374 --> 00:05:36.377
The urgent care bill has a late fee on it.

97
00:05:36.461 --> 00:05:38.504
And while we're here. just to say it.

98
00:05:38.588 --> 00:05:42.800
um. your parking tickets
are going into collections.

99
00:05:45.678 --> 00:05:47.847
Are there any subscriptions we can cancel?

100
00:05:47.930 --> 00:05:51.142
Mm. there's that app we signed up for
to help us with our finances.

101
00:05:51.225 --> 00:05:53.353
Yeah. yeah. cancel that.
Cancel everything.

102
00:05:53.436 --> 00:05:54.937
-[distant train horn blares]
-Okay.

103
00:05:55.021 --> 00:06:00.318
So it's 27.795 now.

104
00:06:00.401 --> 00:06:01.235
[exhales sharply]

105
00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:03.571
Thank God I started working full-time.

106
00:06:03.654 --> 00:06:04.989
[rumbling]

107
00:06:05.073 --> 00:06:07.742
We're never gonna be able to afford IVF.

108
00:06:08.242 --> 00:06:09.494
That was a train. right?

109
00:06:09.994 --> 00:06:11.662
Felt a little earthquakey.

110
00:06:12.163 --> 00:06:14.082
Why aren't you more upset about this?

111
00:06:14.916 --> 00:06:17.377
Don't you care about having a baby?

112
00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:20.963
Of course I care. Ash.

113
00:06:21.047 --> 00:06:24.467
I'm just wondering if maybe we should
save up first for food. water?

114
00:06:25.176 --> 00:06:27.720
The Brita filter's lived here
longer than we have.

115
00:06:30.807 --> 00:06:34.769
Okay. well. I'll steal some waters
at the club tomorrow.

116
00:06:35.269 --> 00:06:36.896
I mean. I don't know.

117
00:06:36.979 --> 00:06:43.444
Maybe this is the universe. like.
telling us to slow down. you know?

118
00:06:43.945 --> 00:06:45.405
We're not even married yet.

119
00:06:47.365 --> 00:06:49.283
I still want to. of course.

120
00:06:49.367 --> 00:06:52.161
We can get married at the courthouse.
We can do that anytime.

121
00:06:52.245 --> 00:06:55.039
Babe. why are we rushing everything?

122
00:06:55.123 --> 00:06:56.791
[scoffs] I'm not.

123
00:06:57.291 --> 00:06:59.794
This is just all part of being an adult.

124
00:07:00.795 --> 00:07:04.215
I'm just trying to make sure
I can give us what we need.

125
00:07:04.298 --> 00:07:07.260
Yeah. but let's take our time with it

126
00:07:07.343 --> 00:07:11.264
and. like. enjoy our lives. you know?

127
00:07:12.390 --> 00:07:15.393
I mean. we haven't even been down
to the beach once this month.

128
00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:17.645
I know. you're right.

129
00:07:18.146 --> 00:07:19.355
We can go Sunday.

130
00:07:20.022 --> 00:07:21.065
I guess I just…

131
00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:23.609
I kind of feel like it'll all go away
if we don't.

132
00:07:23.693 --> 00:07:25.486
and I know that's stupid.

133
00:07:25.570 --> 00:07:26.779
It's not stupid.

134
00:07:27.280 --> 00:07:28.823
You're just stressed.

135
00:07:29.907 --> 00:07:31.909
[pensive music playing]

136
00:07:32.493 --> 00:07:34.454
Can I do our daily check early?

137
00:07:36.581 --> 00:07:38.458
Mm-hmm. of course.

138
00:07:43.337 --> 00:07:46.466
I know this is unhealthy.
but it really does help me so much.

139
00:07:46.549 --> 00:07:49.886
Mm. I get it.
I gotta earn that trust back.

140
00:07:49.969 --> 00:07:51.721
Who the fuck is 415…

141
00:07:52.221 --> 00:07:53.848
Oh. wait. it's DoorDash. [chuckles]

142
00:07:54.348 --> 00:07:55.308
Sorry.

143
00:08:00.938 --> 00:08:04.734
Okay. Uh. so as we continue to build out
the wellness center.

144
00:08:04.817 --> 00:08:10.031
we'll be temporarily using the pro shop
to sell Trochos products.

145
00:08:10.948 --> 00:08:15.912
Uh. members can sign up for procedures
at the Seoul clinic with any employee.

146
00:08:15.995 --> 00:08:20.291
and for each sale.
you'll be entitled to a 10% commission.

147
00:08:20.374 --> 00:08:21.959
Oh. just saw Calvin perk up.

148
00:08:22.043 --> 00:08:23.920
[Calvin] You know it. I need that money.

149
00:08:24.003 --> 00:08:25.046
Yeah.

150
00:08:25.129 --> 00:08:27.840
You and me both. Calvin. You and me both.

151
00:08:28.341 --> 00:08:31.594
Uh. so for any questions.
just go ahead and ask Woosh.

152
00:08:31.677 --> 00:08:35.473
who is running late again.
and he'll set you up.

153
00:08:35.556 --> 00:08:38.684
All right?
Let's go out there and be team MVP.

154
00:08:39.185 --> 00:08:43.523
They want to add
a body composition analyzer there. yeah?

155
00:08:43.606 --> 00:08:44.649
That's correct. yes.

156
00:08:44.732 --> 00:08:46.734
[Eunice] Around how much would that cost?

157
00:08:46.817 --> 00:08:49.529
3K. 5. some go higher.

158
00:08:50.029 --> 00:08:53.616
[Eunice] There's no way
it'd be 75K. right?

159
00:08:53.699 --> 00:08:55.451
You know.
Ashley's really good with numbers

160
00:08:55.535 --> 00:08:58.120
if you need help
keeping track of everything.

161
00:08:58.204 --> 00:08:59.413
That's nice.

162
00:08:59.497 --> 00:09:02.708
Now. why did we replace
the old ellipticals?

163
00:09:02.792 --> 00:09:04.794
Are Precors that different
from other brands?

164
00:09:04.877 --> 00:09:06.295
Hey. is everything okay?

165
00:09:09.257 --> 00:09:10.341
Yes. of course.

166
00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:13.803
I just have a lot on my plate right now.

167
00:09:18.933 --> 00:09:22.061
Look. I know we haven't talked that much
since the hospital.

168
00:09:22.144 --> 00:09:23.479
but it's not 'cause I don't care.

169
00:09:24.605 --> 00:09:29.193
Ashley's gone through a lot
this past month. so I gotta focus on her.

170
00:09:29.277 --> 00:09:31.529
But if you ever wanna

171
00:09:32.154 --> 00:09:33.698
talk about anything.

172
00:09:34.407 --> 00:09:35.616
you can always hit me up.

173
00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:37.118
Anytime.

174
00:09:38.953 --> 00:09:40.037
Before dinner.

175
00:09:40.746 --> 00:09:42.582
And maybe in. like. a public setting.

176
00:09:45.293 --> 00:09:46.627
No.

177
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:49.088
I'm okay. honestly.

178
00:09:49.171 --> 00:09:50.506
[Eunice chuckles]

179
00:09:51.215 --> 00:09:53.759
I think that's all the questions I had.

180
00:09:53.843 --> 00:09:55.845
[pensive music playing]

181
00:10:02.685 --> 00:10:04.687
[children playfully screaming]

182
00:10:08.899 --> 00:10:09.900
What the hell is this?

183
00:10:10.484 --> 00:10:11.319
[woman] Lindsay!

184
00:10:11.402 --> 00:10:13.070
-Oh my God. Hi!
-[man] Hey!

185
00:10:13.154 --> 00:10:15.865
I can't believe she's 6.
Where does the time go?

186
00:10:15.948 --> 00:10:19.076
It's so good to see you.
We didn't know you were coming.

187
00:10:19.160 --> 00:10:21.746
Oh. well. Grace's birthday is
on my calendar every year.

188
00:10:21.829 --> 00:10:24.582
I just wanted to make up
for missing the last few.

189
00:10:24.665 --> 00:10:26.709
Oh. well. thank you so much.

190
00:10:26.792 --> 00:10:29.712
You should put this in the shade.
It's gonna start expanding in the heat.

191
00:10:29.795 --> 00:10:30.755
Oh. Okay.

192
00:10:31.464 --> 00:10:35.176
Well. it is so good to see you.
Food and drinks are right over there.

193
00:10:35.259 --> 00:10:36.510
Oh. she looks amazing.

194
00:10:36.594 --> 00:10:38.846
Sorry. just…
Meredith. I had a quick question.

195
00:10:38.929 --> 00:10:43.267
Um. hypothetically.
if a couple was getting divorced.

196
00:10:43.351 --> 00:10:45.603
um. and one of them
was up for a promotion.

197
00:10:46.103 --> 00:10:49.231
how does that work
if the paperwork isn't signed yet?

198
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:50.775
-Oh!
-Oh my God!

199
00:10:50.858 --> 00:10:52.568
-Jimmy!
-[Jimmy laughs]

200
00:10:54.236 --> 00:10:56.280
It doesn't look like Lindsay liked that.

201
00:10:56.364 --> 00:10:59.617
Everyone is in charge of
their own body. remember?

202
00:10:59.700 --> 00:11:01.744
[playfully screams]

203
00:11:02.953 --> 00:11:03.788
I'm so sorry.

204
00:11:03.871 --> 00:11:05.790
He's grown so much. It's. um…

205
00:11:06.290 --> 00:11:08.626
Well. when's his birthday?
Gotta get that in the calendar.

206
00:11:08.709 --> 00:11:10.336
Oh. you don't need to do that.

207
00:11:10.419 --> 00:11:12.171
I should actually
go grab that snake from him.

208
00:11:12.254 --> 00:11:13.798
Sorry. so just real quick.

209
00:11:13.881 --> 00:11:16.008
So in that hypothetical scenario.

210
00:11:16.092 --> 00:11:18.427
can the wife be entitled
to future earnings

211
00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:22.014
if she helped foster the relationships
that led to the promotion?

212
00:11:22.098 --> 00:11:23.724
It depends on a lot of things.

213
00:11:23.808 --> 00:11:25.935
When they separated.
the nature of the contract…

214
00:11:26.018 --> 00:11:28.729
California courts typically
don't split future wages.

215
00:11:29.313 --> 00:11:34.485
Right. Well. my. um. friend Penelope
is getting divorced.

216
00:11:34.568 --> 00:11:35.903
-[Meredith] Mm.
-It's really sad.

217
00:11:35.986 --> 00:11:38.447
Um. and she said that ChatGPT said

218
00:11:38.531 --> 00:11:40.991
that she could prove her contributions
in court.

219
00:11:41.951 --> 00:11:44.078
I should get going.
It was so great to see--

220
00:11:44.161 --> 00:11:46.288
Sorry. just real…
Last thing. I promise. Um…

221
00:11:46.372 --> 00:11:49.041
Sorry. Penelope had a few more questions.
I just wrote a little list.

222
00:11:49.625 --> 00:11:51.836
Uh. I guess. just. you know.
is there anything else

223
00:11:51.919 --> 00:11:54.380
that she could possibly do
to help her cause?

224
00:11:54.463 --> 00:11:58.342
Um. she might be able to get a hold
of an incriminating video of her husband.

225
00:11:58.426 --> 00:11:59.844
It's a bit complicated…

226
00:11:59.927 --> 00:12:04.181
If Penelope wants to chat more.
she can set a time for my office.

227
00:12:04.265 --> 00:12:07.643
Uh. Penelope's a little tight on money.
so just to ask it. what's your rate again?

228
00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:09.270
[Jimmy grunts. screams]

229
00:12:09.353 --> 00:12:11.188
-Jimmy. it's such a fun game!
-[Jimmy] No! No!

230
00:12:11.272 --> 00:12:12.815
[Jimmy groans. whines]

231
00:12:12.898 --> 00:12:14.567
What do you need. sweetie?

232
00:12:14.650 --> 00:12:16.736
I want her to go on the bounce house!

233
00:12:16.819 --> 00:12:18.654
Oh. I don't know about that. I'm--

234
00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:20.656
[Jimmy screams]

235
00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:22.324
[scream continues]

236
00:12:22.408 --> 00:12:23.409
[Meredith chuckles]

237
00:12:23.492 --> 00:12:25.035
[Meredith] Please? [chuckles]

238
00:12:25.119 --> 00:12:28.497
[Jimmy screaming]

239
00:12:29.415 --> 00:12:32.501
Uh. sorry for the delay. fellas.
That eucalyptus mist should kick in now.

240
00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:33.836
And lunches are comped on me.

241
00:12:33.919 --> 00:12:36.297
[Troy] Ah. appreciate you. Josh.

242
00:12:36.797 --> 00:12:38.466
-You're the man. Troy.
-[man 1] Hey. Josh!

243
00:12:38.549 --> 00:12:41.385
I heard
Lindsay stopped by Gracie's birthday.

244
00:12:41.886 --> 00:12:43.220
-Oh. yeah?
-[man 1] Yeah.

245
00:12:43.304 --> 00:12:45.181
Uh. sorry. who's… who's that speaking?

246
00:12:45.264 --> 00:12:46.390
It's Paul.

247
00:12:46.474 --> 00:12:48.726
Oh. yes. Paul. Of course. yeah.

248
00:12:48.809 --> 00:12:50.853
Oh. I didn't realize
Lindsay was stopping by.

249
00:12:50.936 --> 00:12:54.690
