00:24:15.203 --> 00:24:17.164
You always have the best style.

496
00:24:17.247 --> 00:24:19.708
[Eunice chuckles]
That's so nice of you to say.

497
00:24:19.791 --> 00:24:21.668
I love your style as well.

498
00:24:22.169 --> 00:24:24.087
Yay. shopping date. [chuckles]

499
00:24:24.171 --> 00:24:25.964
Yay! [chuckles]

500
00:24:28.216 --> 00:24:29.342
So what's up?

501
00:24:30.177 --> 00:24:31.928
So I was wondering.

502
00:24:32.429 --> 00:24:35.098
do you happen to archive
old invoices here?

503
00:24:35.765 --> 00:24:39.728
Uh. no. that's off-site with finance.
But what are you looking for?

504
00:24:40.353 --> 00:24:43.482
I just wanted to check a few payments
that went out to Korea.

505
00:24:43.565 --> 00:24:44.399
Oh. yeah.

506
00:24:44.483 --> 00:24:47.444
Sorry. you have to go through finance
and get Josh's approval for that.

507
00:24:47.527 --> 00:24:48.737
I see.

508
00:24:49.613 --> 00:24:52.032
So there's nothing at all?

509
00:24:52.532 --> 00:24:53.867
Sorry.

510
00:24:55.327 --> 00:24:56.536
Is everything okay?

511
00:24:56.620 --> 00:24:58.538
Yeah. no. everything's fine.

512
00:24:59.039 --> 00:24:59.915
[clears throat]

513
00:25:03.543 --> 00:25:04.628
You know what?

514
00:25:04.711 --> 00:25:08.006
I did take a picture of some last month.
One sec.

515
00:25:08.757 --> 00:25:10.800
I looked up the names.
and they were staff at Trochos.

516
00:25:10.884 --> 00:25:13.553
so I figured it was all
part of. like. setting everything up here.

517
00:25:13.637 --> 00:25:15.972
Oh. that's so helpful. Thank you so much.

518
00:25:16.056 --> 00:25:17.349
Oh! Here it is.

519
00:25:17.849 --> 00:25:20.560
And please tell Austin thank you as well

520
00:25:20.644 --> 00:25:22.729
for going over
all the equipment yesterday.

521
00:25:24.314 --> 00:25:25.148
Oh. yeah?

522
00:25:25.232 --> 00:25:29.611
I know you two have so much going on.
so I appreciate you taking the time.

523
00:25:29.694 --> 00:25:31.821
Aw. of course.

524
00:25:32.989 --> 00:25:34.824
You know what? I'm just now remembering.

525
00:25:34.908 --> 00:25:36.826
I should probably run this by Woosh first.

526
00:25:36.910 --> 00:25:40.205
since he's kind of running point
on all the Trochos stuff and whatnot.

527
00:25:40.288 --> 00:25:43.208
Oh. well. you can just send me the photo.
and I can talk to him.

528
00:25:43.708 --> 00:25:44.834
Um…

529
00:25:45.377 --> 00:25:47.587
Yeah. no. I'd rather not.

530
00:25:48.255 --> 00:25:50.590
Ooh. I've got to take this.
It's the doctor.

531
00:25:51.424 --> 00:25:52.884
Austin and I are doing IVF.

532
00:25:58.598 --> 00:25:59.891
Hi. Doctor.

533
00:26:01.893 --> 00:26:03.103
[Austin] <i>If you think about it.</i>

534
00:26:03.186 --> 00:26:06.565
the modern workplace has eliminated
most of our rotational movement.

535
00:26:06.648 --> 00:26:08.984
Yeah. I mean. that makes sense
'cause we sit all day.

536
00:26:09.067 --> 00:26:11.152
-[Austin] Yep.
-I hadn't thought about that. Thank you.

537
00:26:11.236 --> 00:26:12.654
-[Austin] You're welcome.
-[groans]

538
00:26:13.154 --> 00:26:16.199
So… tell me
a little bit more about yourself. man.

539
00:26:16.283 --> 00:26:17.659
You played football?

540
00:26:18.243 --> 00:26:20.537
-Yeah. at ASU.
-All four years?

541
00:26:20.620 --> 00:26:22.414
All right. let's switch over
to the other side.

542
00:26:22.497 --> 00:26:26.251
I got injured in my junior year
after I won the Butkus Award in 2015.

543
00:26:26.334 --> 00:26:27.502
That's too bad.

544
00:26:27.586 --> 00:26:29.504
-I'm just gonna warn you.
-Yep.

545
00:26:29.588 --> 00:26:32.757
Due to my high basal metabolic rate.
I may sweat on you.

546
00:26:32.841 --> 00:26:33.800
Yeah.

547
00:26:35.385 --> 00:26:36.261
It's all good. man.

548
00:26:36.845 --> 00:26:38.138
So you got injured.

549
00:26:38.221 --> 00:26:40.849
and then you started pursuing
your physical therapy degree?

550
00:26:41.349 --> 00:26:43.893
Mm-hmm.
Your thoracic spine's pretty rigid.

551
00:26:43.977 --> 00:26:47.731
I tweaked it… a long time ago.
so it's probably holding on to that.

552
00:26:47.814 --> 00:26:51.985
Hey. man. so I hear Lindsay and Ashley
have been spending a lot of time together.

553
00:26:52.068 --> 00:26:54.446
Yeah. she really appreciates
the friendship.

554
00:26:54.529 --> 00:26:56.239
Yeah. that's… that's really nice.

555
00:26:56.740 --> 00:26:59.993
I was a little surprised 'cause
they don't seem to have much in common.

556
00:27:00.744 --> 00:27:02.954
-I wonder what they even talk about.
-Right.

557
00:27:03.038 --> 00:27:04.289
Like. what do they talk about?

558
00:27:04.372 --> 00:27:05.373
[both chuckle]

559
00:27:05.874 --> 00:27:07.626
Um. let me look back here?

560
00:27:07.709 --> 00:27:09.669
Yeah. yeah. go for it.
Get in there. Please.

561
00:27:09.753 --> 00:27:14.507
You know… chronic pain is
a physical manifestation

562
00:27:14.591 --> 00:27:17.969
of the emotional interior. they say.

563
00:27:18.678 --> 00:27:19.846
-Is that right?
-Mm-hmm.

564
00:27:20.722 --> 00:27:22.432
-Huh.
-Mind-body connection.

565
00:27:22.515 --> 00:27:24.225
Thank you. Wow. you're very good.

566
00:27:24.309 --> 00:27:26.394
-Ooh! Very good. yeah.
-Thank you.

567
00:27:26.478 --> 00:27:27.354
Yeah.

568
00:27:27.437 --> 00:27:30.106
Hey. do you know…
do you know anything about cold plunges?

569
00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:31.483
-Yeah. Yeah.
-Yeah?

570
00:27:31.566 --> 00:27:34.235
Troy gifted me one a while back.
and I haven't put it together yet.

571
00:27:34.319 --> 00:27:37.405
Oh my God. I can help you
put that together easy.

572
00:27:37.489 --> 00:27:38.448
Yeah?

573
00:27:38.531 --> 00:27:39.491
Yeah.

574
00:27:40.033 --> 00:27:41.034
Let's do it.

575
00:27:41.826 --> 00:27:42.869
Fo sho.

576
00:27:45.747 --> 00:27:47.332
And then Troy took me to Napa.

577
00:27:47.415 --> 00:27:50.585
and we had the most magical meal
I've ever had in my life.

578
00:27:50.669 --> 00:27:53.254
Oh my God. that's so romantic.

579
00:27:53.338 --> 00:27:56.800
Right? I don't know what I did
in a past life to get this lucky.

580
00:27:57.759 --> 00:27:59.177
-Shit.
-[whispers] That's not luck.

581
00:27:59.260 --> 00:28:01.096
It's because she's such a good person.

582
00:28:01.596 --> 00:28:02.555
[Ava] I can do this.

583
00:28:02.639 --> 00:28:04.641
Uh. I don't think it's luck. Ava.

584
00:28:04.724 --> 00:28:06.685
I think it's 'cause
you're such a good person.

585
00:28:07.268 --> 00:28:10.647
Aw. Ash. you're so sweet.

586
00:28:13.441 --> 00:28:15.860
You know what? Fuck it.
I'm just gonna bring the ball up. okay?

587
00:28:15.944 --> 00:28:17.237
[Lindsay] Oh my gosh. yeah.

588
00:28:17.737 --> 00:28:20.740
Sand should only belong on the beach.
I always say.

589
00:28:20.824 --> 00:28:24.828
Linds. did you see how everyone's
signing up for those Trochos packages?

590
00:28:25.328 --> 00:28:28.540
-You don't think I need it. right?
-Oh my God. no. You look so young.

591
00:28:29.040 --> 00:28:31.710
Yeah… you look younger than me. even.

592
00:28:31.793 --> 00:28:33.920
Stop. Now I know you're lying.

593
00:28:34.003 --> 00:28:36.840
I mean. I probably don't need it. Right?

594
00:28:38.341 --> 00:28:39.843
-No. Oh my God. no.
-Definitely not.

595
00:28:41.052 --> 00:28:41.886
Right.

596
00:28:44.764 --> 00:28:47.183
I was thinking.
actually. of signing up myself.

597
00:28:47.684 --> 00:28:49.978
Ashley was gonna walk me through it later.

598
00:28:50.061 --> 00:28:51.771
You can come along if you want.

599
00:28:52.564 --> 00:28:55.942
Okay. Yeah. I'd just be curious
what it all entails.

600
00:28:56.443 --> 00:28:57.902
Yeah. I mean. you don't need it.

601
00:28:57.986 --> 00:28:59.362
But. you know. if you're into it.

602
00:28:59.446 --> 00:29:01.781
you can just say you're coming with me
for emotional support.

603
00:29:01.865 --> 00:29:03.032
and no one will ever know.

604
00:29:03.116 --> 00:29:05.285
Ashley will do everything very discreetly.
Right. Ash?

605
00:29:05.368 --> 00:29:06.786
Oh. totally. Super discreet.

606
00:29:06.870 --> 00:29:09.330
Oh my God. that would be so magical.

607
00:29:09.414 --> 00:29:12.959
Well. Ashley needs the double commission.
She's starting IVF with Dr. Shin.

608
00:29:13.042 --> 00:29:15.253
-Dr. Shin?
-[Lindsay] Yeah.

609
00:29:16.504 --> 00:29:18.173
I mean. he's the best. right?

610
00:29:18.256 --> 00:29:19.758
Yeah. Dr. Shin. Uh…

611
00:29:20.258 --> 00:29:22.927
Miracle hands is what they told us.

612
00:29:23.011 --> 00:29:26.681
Well. I don't know who told you that.
but my cousin is the best in the country.

613
00:29:26.765 --> 00:29:29.934
-Did you already start with Dr. Shin?
-No. not yet.

614
00:29:30.435 --> 00:29:33.146
I'll connect you with my cousin.
She'll see you right away.

615
00:29:33.229 --> 00:29:35.106
-[golf club hits ball]
-Fuck!

616
00:29:35.190 --> 00:29:36.900
[intriguing music playing]

617
00:29:36.983 --> 00:29:39.861
[Austin] Yeah. man.
It's good we're finally setting this up.

618
00:29:39.944 --> 00:29:42.697
As a certified physical therapist.
I plunge all the time.

619
00:29:42.781 --> 00:29:47.202
Like. I'm super familiar
with all the benefits and what have you.

620
00:29:48.244 --> 00:29:49.746
Cold's good for the body.

621
00:29:49.829 --> 00:29:51.706
-Hot's good as well.
-Mm.

622
00:29:51.790 --> 00:29:53.833
-You can mix it up.
-Yeah.

623
00:29:53.917 --> 00:29:56.586
In which order? Depends on varying factors
that I won't get into now.

624
00:29:57.462 --> 00:29:59.839
At the end of the day.
it's all about information.

625
00:29:59.923 --> 00:30:02.550
Well. this is so helpful. brother.

626
00:30:02.634 --> 00:30:04.803
-Really. really appreciate it.
-Anytime.

627
00:30:05.428 --> 00:30:07.931
All things wellness. I'm your guy.

628
00:30:08.014 --> 00:30:08.890
Ah.

629
00:30:09.390 --> 00:30:11.643
I mean. is there anything
that I can help <i>you </i>out with?

630
00:30:11.726 --> 00:30:13.311
Like. what's going on with you?

631
00:30:14.062 --> 00:30:15.980
No. I'm good.

632
00:30:16.064 --> 00:30:18.566
Just… digging in. Day by day.

633
00:30:18.650 --> 00:30:19.567
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

634
00:30:19.651 --> 00:30:21.152
And how are things with Ashley?

635
00:30:21.236 --> 00:30:24.447
Like. is everything… everything okay
on that front?

636
00:30:24.531 --> 00:30:26.699
Uh. everything's great. We're great.

637
00:30:26.783 --> 00:30:27.742
Good.

638
00:30:27.826 --> 00:30:29.911
-Yeah. It's really awesome.
-Yeah.

639
00:30:29.994 --> 00:30:32.455
Well. I know
that we all started off on the wrong foot.

640
00:30:32.539 --> 00:30:33.373
Mm-hmm.

641
00:30:33.456 --> 00:30:38.586
And I'm just so happy
that all that's behind us now. Right?

642
00:30:39.712 --> 00:30:41.422
Yeah. Me too.

643
00:30:42.006 --> 00:30:43.049
Yeah.

644
00:30:43.132 --> 00:30:46.302
I'm just gonna get a few more things
and get out of here.

645
00:30:46.386 --> 00:30:47.303
Yep.

646
00:30:55.770 --> 00:30:57.397
Is this. uh. part of the setup?

647
00:30:58.106 --> 00:30:59.023
Oh!

648
00:30:59.732 --> 00:31:02.110
Oh yeah! I forgot about that.

649
00:31:02.193 --> 00:31:04.195
Yeah. Troy gave me this with the plunge.

650
00:31:04.279 --> 00:31:06.155
Have you… have you ever heard of bufo?

651
00:31:06.239 --> 00:31:08.032
[scoffs] Bro.

652
00:31:08.616 --> 00:31:10.910
-Are you familiar?
-Oh. I'm familiar.

653
00:31:10.994 --> 00:31:11.828
Is it crazy?

654
00:31:11.911 --> 00:31:13.037
Nah. it's chill.

655
00:31:13.121 --> 00:31:14.497
-Really?
-Yeah.

656
00:31:15.206 --> 00:31:18.293
'Cause Troy said it'd cure
all of my neurosis in. like. ten minutes.

657
00:31:18.376 --> 00:31:20.503
Yeah. man. I've seen it happen in eight.

658
00:31:20.587 --> 00:31:22.088
-Really?
-Yeah.

659
00:31:22.171 --> 00:31:23.089
Oh.

660
00:31:24.132 --> 00:31:27.218
I mean. I just wouldn't wanna
do it alone. though. you know.

661
00:31:27.302 --> 00:31:28.177
[Austin] Mm.

662
00:31:29.262 --> 00:31:31.431
Let me move some things around.
I'm here for you.

663
00:31:31.514 --> 00:31:33.016
-For real?
-For real.

664
00:31:33.099 --> 00:31:34.642
[both chuckle]

665
00:31:47.614 --> 00:31:51.075
And it's all-inclusive
with the millennial makeover package.

666
00:31:51.159 --> 00:31:52.827
-Right. Woosh?
-[Woosh] Yep.

667
00:31:52.911 --> 00:31:56.331
Hey. so this invoice you sent me
was from last month. yeah?

668
00:31:56.414 --> 00:31:59.250
Uh. yeah. Eunice said she needed to check
the numbers or something.

669
00:31:59.334 --> 00:32:00.960
so I figured
you'd know what to do with it.

670
00:32:02.879 --> 00:32:07.300
Thanks. Yeah. I know exactly what to do.
I'll be right back.

671
00:32:08.134 --> 00:32:11.220
So what do you think. Ava?
Should I go for the whole package?

672
00:32:11.304 --> 00:32:13.264
Only if you feel comfortable.

673
00:32:13.348 --> 00:32:14.307
[door closes]

674
00:32:14.390 --> 00:32:15.808
Yeah. sleep on it.

675
00:32:15.892 --> 00:32:17.560
You can always start with one area.

676
00:32:18.061 --> 00:32:21.814
But I will say that most people end up
wishing they did the whole package.

677
00:32:21.898 --> 00:32:23.107
It's such a long flight. right?

678
00:32:23.191 --> 00:32:25.068
You have to pay
for the recovery fee each time.

679
00:32:25.151 --> 00:32:26.235
[Ashley] Exactly.

680
00:32:27.570 --> 00:32:31.199
And are we sure that this doctor
is as good as Dr. Kim?

681
00:32:31.908 --> 00:32:34.827
I mean. some people say he's even better.

682
00:32:34.911 --> 00:32:37.705
He only does Korean actors and pop stars.

683
00:32:37.789 --> 00:32:39.749
Wow. so cool.

684
00:32:40.792 --> 00:32:42.585
-And Shakira.
-[Ava] Shakira?

685
00:32:42.669 --> 00:32:47.006
Oh my. And is it business class or coach?
And where do we stay?

686
00:32:47.090 --> 00:32:50.468
Oh. the tickets are business class.
And you stay at a five-star hotel.

687
00:32:50.551 --> 00:32:53.096
Wait. what?
All that's included in the package?

688
00:32:53.805 --> 00:32:55.306
Black car service too.

689
00:32:55.390 --> 00:32:58.017
Uh. fine. Let me see this menu.

690
00:33:01.229 --> 00:33:03.773
Okay. I actually want all of this.

691
00:33:03.856 --> 00:33:06.109
But if anyone ever finds out.
I will kill you.

692
00:33:06.985 --> 00:33:10.530
No one's gonna find out from us.
You're just my emotional support. right?

693
00:33:12.281 --> 00:33:15.576
[Ava squeals]
We're doing a girls' trip. Troy's paying.

694
00:33:16.703 --> 00:33:19.455
[wheezy exhale]

695
00:33:23.501 --> 00:33:24.752
You okay. brother?

696
00:33:28.297 --> 00:33:30.383
[moans] Your… your turn. brother.

697
00:33:31.801 --> 00:33:33.219
Bro. I'm gonna hold off for now

698
00:33:33.302 --> 00:33:36.180
'cause I wanna make sure
to guide you to a good place. okay?

699
00:33:36.264 --> 00:33:37.140
Okay.

700
00:33:37.223 --> 00:33:39.475
Any moment now.
you should experience a whiteout

701
00:33:39.559 --> 00:33:42.520
where you disappear
and all that remains is love.

702
00:33:43.312 --> 00:33:45.940
Just take a few more hits
and try to break through. okay?

703
00:33:46.024 --> 00:33:47.191
Okay.

704
00:33:48.818 --> 00:33:50.820
[inhales deeply]

705
00:33:52.947 --> 00:33:54.949
[dreamy ethereal music playing]

706
00:33:58.536 --> 00:34:00.913
[exhales sharply]

707
00:34:03.624 --> 00:34:05.418
[breathing heavily]

708
00:34:05.501 --> 00:34:07.086
Austin. Austin.

709
00:34:08.212 --> 00:34:10.214
[breathy exhale]

710
00:34:11.466 --> 00:34:12.508
Linds?

711
00:34:13.384 --> 00:34:16.304
-[Lindsay] It's okay. darling. I love you.
-[giggles]

712
00:34:16.387 --> 00:34:17.221
Mama.

713
00:34:17.305 --> 00:34:19.515
[in Spanish] It's okay. my boy.

714
00:34:19.599 --> 00:34:22.435
You don't have to try so hard.

715
00:34:22.518 --> 00:34:24.145
I love you.

716
00:34:24.645 --> 00:34:29.025
[in English] I love you.
no matter what. <i>mijito</i>.

717
00:34:31.527 --> 00:34:32.361
Mama.

718
00:34:32.445 --> 00:34:35.823
[in Spanish] I have to tell you something.
It's very important.

719
00:34:36.991 --> 00:34:38.993
[unsettling music playing]

720
00:34:39.911 --> 00:34:41.913
[crying]

721
00:34:44.040 --> 00:34:45.917
[screaming]

722
00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:49.087
[euphoric moaning]

723
00:34:51.464 --> 00:34:54.884
[euphoric moaning]

724
00:34:57.804 --> 00:35:00.723
[in English] I just saw every woman
that I've ever slept with.

725
00:35:03.017 --> 00:35:05.353
And then my mom became me.

726
00:35:06.896 --> 00:35:08.314
Yeah. man.

727
00:35:08.397 --> 00:35:09.732
That's bufo.

728
00:35:10.608 --> 00:35:11.526
Bufo.

729
00:35:13.820 --> 00:35:14.821
No.

730
00:35:16.030 --> 00:35:17.323
No. it's me.

731
00:35:18.241 --> 00:35:19.617
It's me. I… I…

732
00:35:20.409 --> 00:35:21.869
I did this to myself.

733
00:35:22.370 --> 00:35:25.123
I might have given you
the wrong dose. man.

734
00:35:25.623 --> 00:35:27.458
It's not your fault. okay?

735
00:35:28.876 --> 00:35:31.379
Austin. can I be honest with you?

736
00:35:31.462 --> 00:35:33.714
I invited you over here

737
00:35:34.423 --> 00:35:38.636
to try to convince you
to delete the backup videos of the fight.

738
00:35:39.137 --> 00:35:40.096
Oh.

739
00:35:40.763 --> 00:35:42.723
Lindsay and I are getting divorced.

740
00:35:44.183 --> 00:35:45.101
I'm sorry.

741
00:35:45.601 --> 00:35:47.019
I think we all saw it coming.

742
00:35:48.521 --> 00:35:50.898
I was gonna try to get to the video
before she did.

743
00:35:51.816 --> 00:35:54.235
I thought
I could get it from you on drugs.

744
00:35:55.611 --> 00:35:58.114
It's… it's fucking pathetic.

745
00:35:58.197 --> 00:35:59.365
[chuckles]

746
00:36:00.491 --> 00:36:02.618
Damn. that would've worked.

747
00:36:03.911 --> 00:36:04.912
It's just

748
00:36:05.496 --> 00:36:08.291
I don't know how to get to the other side.

749
00:36:11.002 --> 00:36:11.878
You know?

750
00:36:14.130 --> 00:36:17.508
I feel like there's just so much love.
like. right there.

751
00:36:17.592 --> 00:36:19.302
[ethereal music playing]

752
00:36:19.385 --> 00:36:21.512
But I just… I just can't…

753
00:36:24.056 --> 00:36:26.058
I just can't get there.

754
00:36:27.977 --> 00:36:29.687
A lot of people love you. man.

755
00:36:30.897 --> 00:36:33.065
Everyone at the club loves you.

756
00:36:33.149 --> 00:36:37.278
No. you see. I grasp at all of that.

757
00:36:38.196 --> 00:36:39.113
I steal it.

758
00:36:39.197 --> 00:36:41.365
I steal all of it

759
00:36:41.866 --> 00:36:47.038
to try and. like. construct
this crutch to prop me up.

760
00:36:47.997 --> 00:36:49.582
You know? 'Cause I don't… I can't…

761
00:36:49.665 --> 00:36:52.043
I don't even know how
to stand anymore. you know?

762
00:36:52.126 --> 00:36:53.419
Do you know what I mean?

763
00:36:54.003 --> 00:36:55.338
Yeah. I'm familiar.

764
00:36:55.922 --> 00:36:59.592
Well. whatever your Achilles heel is.
that little spot…

765
00:37:01.886 --> 00:37:05.640
I know you think you've got time
to work on it. and you do.

766
00:37:05.723 --> 00:37:07.725
You actually… You have a lot of time.

767
00:37:07.808 --> 00:37:11.020
But little by little. life's just gonna

768
00:37:11.854 --> 00:37:14.065
chip away at it. you know?

769
00:37:15.066 --> 00:37:18.402
And. you know. you'll think.
"Okay. well. my shit's not so bad."

770
00:37:18.486 --> 00:37:22.031
You know. it's a fleeting thought.

771
00:37:22.114 --> 00:37:25.326
a… a little temptation here and there.

772
00:37:25.409 --> 00:37:29.538
But once I get the job.
then I'm gonna deal with my shit.

773
00:37:29.622 --> 00:37:31.707
But then you've gotta get the promotion.

774
00:37:32.500 --> 00:37:33.501
Right?

775
00:37:33.584 --> 00:37:35.378
And then you gotta get the house.

776
00:37:35.920 --> 00:37:40.508
And then every interaction
becomes about me. me. me.

777
00:37:40.591 --> 00:37:44.637
"If I do this for Troy.
then maybe Troy will help me later."

778
00:37:44.720 --> 00:37:45.805
You start thinking that way

779
00:37:45.888 --> 00:37:48.140
because it's the only way
to keep your head above water.

780
00:37:48.224 --> 00:37:52.228
And then when you finally catch a breath.
and you go to stand on your own two feet.

781
00:37:52.311 --> 00:37:55.273
that Achilles heel is just gonna give out.

782
00:37:56.357 --> 00:37:57.733
And you're gonna fall.

783
00:37:58.442 --> 00:38:01.445
And you're gonna grasp
at everyone around you.

784
00:38:02.238 --> 00:38:03.572
But it's too late.

785
00:38:04.907 --> 00:38:06.242
You're going down.

786
00:38:08.494 --> 00:38:10.621
And that fleeting thought…

787
00:38:12.790 --> 00:38:14.292
is who you are now.

788
00:38:15.793 --> 00:38:17.670
And you're never gonna change.

789
00:38:21.007 --> 00:38:23.259
Uh… Um…

790
00:38:23.968 --> 00:38:25.970
Have you ever. like.

791
00:38:27.263 --> 00:38:28.389
I don't know.

792
00:38:29.765 --> 00:38:32.393
thought about another girl
while you were with Lindsay?

793
00:38:33.269 --> 00:38:34.770
[chuckles] Brother.

794
00:38:37.773 --> 00:38:38.816
Let's talk.

795
00:38:39.358 --> 00:38:40.484
[Lindsay chuckles]

796
00:38:40.568 --> 00:38:45.448
Um. never have I ever slept
with a coworker.

797
00:38:47.283 --> 00:38:49.452
[gasps] What?

798
00:38:50.369 --> 00:38:53.205
-Austin.
-Oh. Aw. boring.

799
00:38:53.289 --> 00:38:55.374
Um… Oh God. at the club?

800
00:38:59.003 --> 00:39:00.421
-Um. right there.
-[gasps]

801
00:39:00.504 --> 00:39:01.422
[chuckles]

802
00:39:01.505 --> 00:39:03.174
Oh my God.

803
00:39:03.257 --> 00:39:04.467
[Ashley laughs]

804
00:39:04.550 --> 00:39:09.597
Josh and I used to literally have sex
on the polo ground at Coachella.

805
00:39:10.097 --> 00:39:12.058
But he would never ever. ever at work.

806
00:39:12.600 --> 00:39:13.851
Really?

807
00:39:13.934 --> 00:39:14.977
-Not even once?
-No.

808
00:39:15.061 --> 00:39:18.647
Although. he has caught Troy and Ava
having sex in the swimming pool.

809
00:39:18.731 --> 00:39:20.733
Oh my God. [groans]

810
00:39:21.484 --> 00:39:22.818
I guess that adds up.

811
00:39:23.652 --> 00:39:24.528
So. like.

812
00:39:25.321 --> 00:39:29.367
Troy and Ava are…
are. like. happily married?

813
00:39:29.450 --> 00:39:32.370
I mean. yeah. I don't know. I guess.

814
00:39:32.453 --> 00:39:35.081
I mean. it's easy. you know. if it's all…

815
00:39:35.790 --> 00:39:39.543
[exhales] …travel
and fancy events and dinner

816
00:39:39.627 --> 00:39:43.255
and. you know. zero drama
because there's zero substance.

817
00:39:44.048 --> 00:39:44.924
Right.

818
00:39:45.007 --> 00:39:47.343
I don't know.
Maybe they've got the right idea.

819
00:39:52.723 --> 00:39:53.599
Anyway.

820
00:39:54.600 --> 00:39:57.103
you. uh. have

821
00:39:58.396 --> 00:39:59.355
the right doctor now.

822
00:39:59.438 --> 00:40:00.272
Mm-hmm.

823
00:40:00.356 --> 00:40:03.275
And you have a way to pay for it.

824
00:40:04.944 --> 00:40:05.903
-Ah!
-Ooh!

825
00:40:06.487 --> 00:40:07.863
To your… Ooh!

826
00:40:07.947 --> 00:40:09.031
Ooh!

827
00:40:09.115 --> 00:40:10.574
…future

828
00:40:11.409 --> 00:40:12.660
baby.

829
00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:15.496
[both] Cheers.

830
00:40:22.545 --> 00:40:23.796
Hey. um…

831
00:40:25.047 --> 00:40:25.965
Uh…

832
00:40:26.590 --> 00:40:28.342
Sorry if this is weird. but. um.

833
00:40:29.969 --> 00:40:32.721
can you tell me
why you're being so nice to me?

834
00:40:34.974 --> 00:40:37.101
I don't know what you're talking about.

835
00:40:39.520 --> 00:40:42.273
All right. I admit I did have an agenda.

836
00:40:43.566 --> 00:40:46.735
I thought I needed something from you.

837
00:40:48.320 --> 00:40:50.030
But I'm realizing that I don't.

838
00:40:52.408 --> 00:40:54.493
And I just want to help

839
00:40:55.619 --> 00:40:56.620
however I can.

840
00:40:56.704 --> 00:40:58.038
No strings attached.

841
00:40:58.789 --> 00:41:01.083
-You sure?
-Yeah. I'm sure.

842
00:41:03.252 --> 00:41:05.629
I feel like we should split
the commissions at least.

843
00:41:05.713 --> 00:41:06.922
No.

844
00:41:07.006 --> 00:41:09.383
You need it for IVF. I'm fine.

845
00:41:17.016 --> 00:41:19.477
Can I ask why you and Josh never had kids?

846
00:41:19.977 --> 00:41:21.228
Uh.

847
00:41:22.062 --> 00:41:22.938
yeah.

848
00:41:24.940 --> 00:41:27.568
No. we did get pregnant once.

849
00:41:28.944 --> 00:41:30.279
But it didn't stick.

850
00:41:33.491 --> 00:41:35.826
-I'm sorry.
-That's all right. It happens.

851
00:41:37.661 --> 00:41:39.497
We've been meaning to try again.

852
00:41:39.997 --> 00:41:42.958
But I think deep down
we probably both knew

853
00:41:43.042 --> 00:41:44.877
it was a temporary Band-Aid.

854
00:41:45.377 --> 00:41:46.712
Band-Aid for what?

855
00:41:48.589 --> 00:41:52.426
For the immense pain of knowing
that you picked the wrong person.

856
00:41:54.595 --> 00:41:55.471
Oh.

857
00:41:57.431 --> 00:41:58.349
Yeah.

858
00:41:58.432 --> 00:41:59.934
[wistful music playing]

859
00:42:00.017 --> 00:42:03.103
Yeah. in hindsight.
there were just so many signs.

860
00:42:03.187 --> 00:42:04.104
You just think.

861
00:42:04.605 --> 00:42:06.815
"How the fuck
did I not realize this sooner?"

862
00:42:06.899 --> 00:42:07.942
What kind of signs?

863
00:42:08.025 --> 00:42:09.818
Oh my God. so many. like.

864
00:42:10.402 --> 00:42:14.031
uh. the constant fighting that you saw.

865
00:42:14.114 --> 00:42:15.157
Um…

866
00:42:16.367 --> 00:42:18.452
The manipulating for attention.

867
00:42:18.536 --> 00:42:21.205
seeking affection
outside of the relationship.

868
00:42:21.872 --> 00:42:24.375
But that's just
normal ups and downs. right?

869
00:42:24.875 --> 00:42:27.294
I mean. don't people say that

870
00:42:28.462 --> 00:42:30.214
you shouldn't be looking
for the right person.

871
00:42:30.297 --> 00:42:32.132
but actually the right <i>wrong </i>person?

872
00:42:32.216 --> 00:42:36.428
Someone who's seen you at your worst
and you've seen them at theirs.

873
00:42:36.512 --> 00:42:38.180
but you still wanna stay?

874
00:42:39.723 --> 00:42:40.766
Yeah. maybe.

875
00:42:42.309 --> 00:42:43.811
Or maybe it's just…

876
00:42:44.562 --> 00:42:46.105
that's just something

877
00:42:46.814 --> 00:42:48.857
people tell themselves because

878
00:42:49.358 --> 00:42:52.152
it's too hard to admit that this thing.

879
00:42:52.236 --> 00:42:57.032
which finally gave your existence
some semblance of meaning.

880
00:42:58.284 --> 00:42:59.994
is just a sham.

881
00:43:03.330 --> 00:43:04.456
'Cause then what?

882
00:43:05.958 --> 00:43:07.835
You know. you're 40 years old

883
00:43:08.627 --> 00:43:10.879
without the faintest idea of who you are.

884
00:43:13.674 --> 00:43:15.092
Nobody wants that.

885
00:43:25.060 --> 00:43:27.271
You sure you want
to have a baby with Austin?

886
00:43:31.233 --> 00:43:32.651
Yeah. no. I'm sure.

887
00:43:36.614 --> 00:43:38.574
Well. let's sign up some more women. then.

888
00:43:43.329 --> 00:43:44.204
Cheers.

889
00:43:44.872 --> 00:43:46.624
[Josh] You're my new best friend. man.

890
00:43:46.707 --> 00:43:47.875
I appreciate the talk. bro.

891
00:43:47.958 --> 00:43:49.752
Yeah. yeah.

892
00:43:49.835 --> 00:43:52.421
-Be kind to yourself. Okay?
-Yeah. Okay.

893
00:43:52.504 --> 00:43:54.923
We're gonna be drawn in
by other frequencies.

894
00:43:55.007 --> 00:43:56.091
[Austin] Mm-hmm.

895
00:43:56.175 --> 00:43:58.218
-Other people. other women.
-Right.

896
00:43:58.302 --> 00:44:01.513
Just let it be. No judgments.

897
00:44:02.014 --> 00:44:03.724
No interpretations. Just…

898
00:44:04.516 --> 00:44:07.227
It's just harmony and dissonance.

899
00:44:07.311 --> 00:44:09.188
Harmony. dissonance.

900
00:44:09.271 --> 00:44:11.607
No. I know.
I just needed to talk it all out.

901
00:44:11.690 --> 00:44:13.984
-Yeah.
-I'm gonna focus on Ashley.

902
00:44:14.068 --> 00:44:15.736
-Yeah.
-Thanks.

903
00:44:21.784 --> 00:44:23.786
All right. [exhales sharply]

904
00:44:26.038 --> 00:44:27.081
Whoo!

905
00:44:29.416 --> 00:44:30.584
[music fades]

906
00:44:30.668 --> 00:44:32.002
[door opens]

907
00:44:32.920 --> 00:44:34.963
-[door closes]
-What the fuck?

908
00:44:38.258 --> 00:44:39.885
Dismantle…

909
00:44:41.345 --> 00:44:42.429
Fuck.

910
00:44:43.639 --> 00:44:44.890
[sighs]

911
00:44:45.599 --> 00:44:47.267
Hey! You're back.

912
00:44:47.351 --> 00:44:48.394
[ethereal music playing]

913
00:44:48.477 --> 00:44:51.563
Uh. sorry. I think you've mistaken me
for someone else.

914
00:44:51.647 --> 00:44:53.857
-Happens all the time.
-No. no. no. no.

915
00:44:53.941 --> 00:44:58.696
I distinctly remember your little car
driving by about a month ago.

916
00:44:59.905 --> 00:45:00.739
What?

917
00:45:00.823 --> 00:45:04.159
I thought to myself.
"What a nice pistachio color."

918
00:45:04.243 --> 00:45:08.914
I even told the Greek guy who lives here.
but he was so upset about his lost dog.

919
00:45:10.290 --> 00:45:11.792
Are you sure it was a Fiat?

920
00:45:11.875 --> 00:45:13.335
I'm pretty sure.

921
00:45:13.419 --> 00:45:16.296
I have the Ring footage on my phone.

922
00:45:19.049 --> 00:45:22.094
Um. may I see the footage. miss?

923
00:45:22.177 --> 00:45:24.096
Are you Polynesian?

924
00:45:26.432 --> 00:45:27.516
Sure.

925
00:45:27.599 --> 00:45:29.476
[in Korean] Beautiful night tonight.

926
00:45:31.311 --> 00:45:33.647
It's too dry. Bad for my skin.

927
00:45:33.731 --> 00:45:35.274
Your skin looks amazing though.

928
00:45:36.525 --> 00:45:39.445
What do you want to discuss?
I don't have time for this.

929
00:45:39.945 --> 00:45:40.863
Of course.

930
00:45:40.988 --> 00:45:43.949
I just wanted you to know that the
authorities in Seoul have contacted me.

931
00:45:44.742 --> 00:45:47.494
About the patient's death at Trochos.

932
00:45:48.912 --> 00:45:52.374
Why would they contact you?
That's very strange.

933
00:45:52.875 --> 00:45:55.127
I know. I found it odd as well.

934
00:45:55.627 --> 00:45:57.629
I have to get ready for dinner.

935
00:45:57.713 --> 00:45:59.339
Will you help me with my necklace?

936
00:46:03.343 --> 00:46:05.387
For now. I said I know nothing.

937
00:46:05.471 --> 00:46:08.974
But if there's something
more specific I should say…

938
00:46:09.683 --> 00:46:11.518
There's nothing to say.

939
00:46:11.602 --> 00:46:15.647
That poor woman died of
a pre-existing condition.

940
00:46:16.648 --> 00:46:19.651
Once they find out you've been bribing
Trochos staff through the club...

941
00:46:20.903 --> 00:46:22.988
...I don't know if that will suffice.

942
00:46:24.239 --> 00:46:26.241
[pensive music playing]

943
00:46:30.871 --> 00:46:32.873
Your father gave this to me.

944
00:46:34.458 --> 00:46:36.335
He always had great taste.

945
00:46:37.669 --> 00:46:41.799
Great taste in fashion. but not in women.

946
00:46:42.633 --> 00:46:44.176
You inherited that.

947
00:46:46.136 --> 00:46:50.641
Chairwoman. I appreciate how
you've kept me afloat all these years...

948
00:46:52.059 --> 00:46:57.356
...but I feel I can do more in life than
manage the tennis shop and sell skincare.

949
00:46:57.856 --> 00:47:00.859
Perhaps you can offer me
a VP position at PK Group?

950
00:47:06.240 --> 00:47:07.199
You...

951
00:47:09.368 --> 00:47:12.287
...look more like your mother
than your father.

952
00:47:13.789 --> 00:47:15.791
I've been told that a lot.

953
00:47:17.626 --> 00:47:20.379
At least you have your father's eyes.

954
00:47:21.672 --> 00:47:24.091
I often wonder...

955
00:47:24.883 --> 00:47:28.512
...what my life would have been like had
your father and I stayed together.

956
00:47:29.596 --> 00:47:32.558
But then I wouldn't exist.

957
00:47:32.641 --> 00:47:34.643
[laughs]

958
00:47:36.019 --> 00:47:37.521
I guess that's true.

959
00:47:41.608 --> 00:47:42.734
Also...

960
00:47:44.152 --> 00:47:47.489
...then you wouldn't have been
VP at PK Electronics.

961
00:47:50.075 --> 00:47:52.870
Let me know when you can start.

962
00:47:53.704 --> 00:47:55.038
Thank you so much. Chairwoman.

963
00:47:55.789 --> 00:47:58.083
Okay. I need to get ready now.

964
00:48:15.559 --> 00:48:17.561
[music intensifies]

965
00:48:21.565 --> 00:48:24.151
["It Takes Time to Be a Man"
by The Rapture playing]

966
00:48:29.948 --> 00:48:30.908
[car engine revs]

967
00:48:30.991 --> 00:48:32.618
-[grunts]
-[tires squeal]

968
00:48:35.746 --> 00:48:39.458
<i>♪ Well. we're all getting bigger ♪</i>

969
00:48:40.709 --> 00:48:44.338
<i>♪ But it takes time to be a man ♪</i>

970
00:48:49.343 --> 00:48:52.971
<i>♪ And it's more than you figure ♪</i>

971
00:48:54.431 --> 00:48:57.851
<i>♪ Well. take it slow and take my hand ♪</i>

972
00:49:02.940 --> 00:49:06.526
<i>♪ And there's room at the mountaintop ♪</i>

973
00:49:07.945 --> 00:49:11.865
<i>♪ For everyone in God's plan ♪</i>

974
00:49:16.370 --> 00:49:19.873
<i>♪ So just trust in your brother ♪</i>

975
00:49:21.541 --> 00:49:25.212
<i>♪ Let me help you if I can ♪</i>

976
00:49:26.713 --> 00:49:28.674
<i>♪ Oh yeah ♪</i>

977
00:49:30.926 --> 00:49:33.470
<i>♪ I bet you can't get what you want ♪</i>

978
00:49:33.553 --> 00:49:37.015
<i>♪ Come on. baby. come on. darling ♪</i>

979
00:49:37.808 --> 00:49:40.560
<i>♪ I bet you can't get what you need ♪</i>

980
00:49:40.644 --> 00:49:44.064
<i>♪ Come on. sugar. and try ♪</i>

981
00:49:44.147 --> 00:49:47.317
<i>♪ And there's faith in the answer ♪</i>

982
00:49:47.401 --> 00:49:48.402
[music fades]

983
